02 czerwiec, 2022

France

France : socio-economic indicators 2014 - 2018

The aim of this report is to present the economy and social conditions in 2014 - 2018 .

Our analysis will be divided on four areas using the following variables:

  • economy:
    • GDP per capita
    • Export as GDP percent
    • Import as GDP percent
    • RD as GDP percent - expenses on research and development expressed as % of GDP
  • Population:
    • population
    • birth rate - total number of live births per 1,000 population
    • life expectation by 65
    • life expectation by birth
  • Unemployment:
    • unemployment rate
    • long term unemployment
  • Women situation:
    • fertility rate - total number of children that would be born to each woman if she were to live to the end of her child-bearing years
    • age at 1st child - mean age of women while giving a birth to 1st child
    • gender pay gap - average difference between the remuneration for men and women who are working expressed in %

The dataset was obtained from Eurostat database.

From the table below we can conclude, that the GDP in the period 2014 - 2018 has changed by 8.38%.

Taking into account the change of population by 0.19% such a change in absolute GDP corresponds to change in GDP per capita by 8.17%.

The maximum and minimum export expressed as GDP percent was observed in 2018 and in 2014 respectively.

The maximum and minimum import expressed as GDP percent was observed in 2018 and in 2014 respectively.

Population

Population per Year

The average population between 2014 and 2018 in France was 65 milions.

The highest population in France was observed in year 2018.

The lowest population in France was observed in year 2014.

Birth rate

The average birth rate between 2014 and 2018 in France was 12.4.

The highest birth rate in France was observed in year 2014.

The lowest birth rate in France was observed in year 2018.

Life expectancy

Life expectancy for people by 65 years old in 2014 was 87.

Life expectancy for people by 65 years old in 2018 was 87.

The average life expectancy between 2014 and 2018 for people by 65 years old in France was 87.

Life expectancy for people by birth in 2014 was 83.

Life expectancy for people by birth in 2018 was 83.

The average life expectancy between 2014 and 2018 for people by birth in France was 82.9.

Short and long term unemployment

Unemployment rate in 2018 was 5.7.

Women situation

Fertility rate

The average fertility rate between 2014 and 2018 in France was 2.

The highest fertility rate in France was observed in year 2014.

The lowest fertility rate in France was observed in year 2018.

Age at first child

The average age of a woman while giving birth to the first child 2014 and 2018 in France was 28.

The highest average age of a woman while giving birth to the first child in France was observed in year 2017.

The lowest average age of a woman while giving birth to the first child in France was observed in year 2014.

Gender pay gap

Gender pay gap is calculated as the average difference between the remuneration for men and women who are working. expressed in %.

The average Gender pay gap between 2014 and 2018 in France was 16 %.

The highest Gender pay gap in France was observed in year 2018.

The lowest Gender pay gap in France was observed in year 2014.
